.|Rangers]] (replay)\n| [[Inverness Caledonian Thistle F.C.|Inverness CT]] vs [[Dundee United F.C.|Dundee United]]\n|-\n| Semi-finals\n| [[Rangers F.C.|Rangers]] vs [[Dundee United F.C.|Dundee United]]<br />[[St Johnstone F.C.|St Johnstone]] vs [[Aberdeen F.C.|Aberdeen]]\n| [[St Johnstone F.C.|St Johnstone]] vs [[Aberdeen F.C.|Aberdeen]]\n|-\n| Final\n| colspan=2 align=center|[[St Johnstone F.C.|St Johnstone]] vs [[Dundee United F.C.|Dundee United]]\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.scottishfa.co.uk/index.cfm?page=1850 Official Site]\n\n{{Scottish Cup seasons}}\n{{2013\u201314 in Scottish football}}\n{{2013\u201314 in European football (UEFA)}}\n{{Portal bar|Association football|Scotland}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:2013-14 Scottish Cup}}\n[[Category:Scottish Cup seasons]]\n[[Category:2013\u201314 in Scottish football cups|1]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2013}}\n{{Use British English|date=August 2013}}\n{{Infobox football tournament season\n| title                      = William Hill Scottish Cup\n| year                       = 2013\u201314\n| other_titles               = \n| image                      = \n| imagesize                  = 240px\n| caption                    = \n| country                    = {{flag|Scotland}}\n| num_teams                  = 82\n| champions                  = [[St Johnstone F.C.|St Johnstone]]\n| runner-up                  = [[Dundee United F.C.|Dundee United]]\n| matches                    = \n| goals                      = \n| top goal scorer            = \n| prevseason                 = [[2012\u201313 Scottish Cup|2012\u201313]]\n| nextseason                 = [[2014\u201315 Scottish Cup|2014\u201315]]\n}}\n\nThe '''2013\u201314 [[Scottish Cup]]''' was the 129th season of Scotland's most prestigious football knockout competition. The tournament will begin on 14 September and end on 17 May 2014. It is sponsored by bookmaker [[William Hill (bookmaker)|William Hill]] in the third season of a five-year partnership after a two-year extension was agreed,<ref>[http://news.williamhill.com/a/football/william-hill-extend-scottish-cup-sponsorship-until-2016/ Scottish Cup sponsorship extension]</ref> and is known as the William Hill Scottish Cup. The winner of the competition qualifies for the second qualifying round of the [[2014\u201315 UEFA Europa League]]. This year will be the first time since the [[1998 Scottish Cup Final]] that the final will be played at [[Celtic Park]].\n\n[[St Johnstone F.C.|St Johnstone]] won their first ever Scottish Cup after a 2-0 win against [[Dundee United F.C.|Dundee United]] in the [[2014 Scottish Cup Final|final]].<ref>{{cite web|url = https://www.telegraph.co.uk/sport/football/competitions/scottish-cup/10838315/Scottish-Cup-final-St-Johnstone-2-Dundee-United-0-match-report.html|title=St Johnstone 2-0 Dundee United|date=17 May 2014|work=Daily Telegraph |accessdate=21 May 2014}}</ref>\t\n\n==Format and calendar==\n\nThirty six clubs enter from the first round, sixteen from the [[Highland Football League|Highland League]], three qualifying [[Scottish Junior Football Association|Junior]] clubs and seventeen other clubs affiliated with the [[Scottish Football Association]].<ref name = \"format\">[http://www.scottishfa.co.uk/resources/documents/ScottishCup/2013-14/WHSC201314Format.pdf Scottish Cup Format]</ref> [[Scottish League Two]] clubs enter in the second round along with the top two clubs from the previous season's [[Highland Football League|Highland League]] and the winners of both the [[South of Scotland Football League|South of Scotland League]] and the [[East of Scotland Football League|East of Scotland League]].<ref name = \"format\"/> [[Scottish League One]] and six [[Scottish Championship]] clubs start in the third round,<ref name = \"format\"/> while the remaining four Championship clubs and all [[Scottish Premiership (association football)|Scottish Premiership]] clubs enter in the fourth round.<ref name = \"format\"/>\n\nThe calendar for the 2013\u201314 competition is as follows:<ref name = \"format\"/>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center\"\n|-\n! rowspan=2|Round\n! rowspan=2|Draw date\n! rowspan=2|First match date\n! colspan=2|Fixtures\n! rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:100px;\"| Clubs\n|-\n! Original\n! Replays\n|-\n| align=left | First round\n| align=left | Thursday 8 August 2013\n| align=left | Saturday 14 September 2013\n| 18\n| 2\n| 82 \u2192 64\n|-\n| align=left | Second round\n| align=left | Monday 16 September 2013\n| align=left | Saturday 5 October 2013\n| 16\n| 6\n| 64 \u2192 48\n|-\n| align=left | Third round\n| align=left |  Monday 7 October 2013\n| align=left | Saturday 2 November 2013\n| 16\n| 3\n| 48 \u2192 32\n|-\n| align=left | Fourth round\n| align=left | Tuesday 5 November 2013\n| align=left | Friday 29 November 2013\n| 16\n| 4\n| 32 \u2192 16\n|-\n| align=left | Fifth round\n| align=left | Monday 2 December 2013\n| align=left | Friday 7 February 2014\n| 8\n| 0\n| 16 \u2192 8\n|-\n| align=left | Quarter-finals\n| align=left | Sunday 9 February 2014\n| align=left | Saturday 8 March 2014\n| 4\n| 1\n| 8 \u2192 4\n|-\n| align=left | Semi-finals\n| align=left | Sunday 9 March 2014\n| align=left | Saturday 12 & Sunday 13 April 2014\n| 2\n| N/A\n| 4 \u2192 2\n|-\n| align=left | Final\n| align=left | N/A\n| align=left | Saturday 17 May 2014\n| 1\n| N/A\n| 2 \u2192 1\n|}\n\n==First round==\n\nThe first round draw took place on 8 August 2013 at the [[Hampden Park]], at 1:15pm.<ref>[http://www.scottishfa.co.uk/scottish_fa_news.cfm?page=1957&newsID=12296&newsCategoryID=1 William Hill Scottish Cup first round draw]</ref>\n\nThis round is contested entirely by non-league clubs:\n* Fifteen SFA full member clubs from the [[Highland Football League]]: ([[Brora Rangers F.C.|Brora Rangers]], [[Buckie Thistle F.C.|Buckie Thistle]], [[Clachnacuddin F.C.|Clachnacuddin]], [[Deveronvale F.C.|Deveronvale]], [[Forres Mechanics F.C.|Forres Mechanics]], [[Fort William F.C.|Fort William]], [[Fraserburgh F.C.|Fraserburgh]], [[Huntly F.C.|Huntly]], [[Inverurie Loco Works F.C.|Inverurie Loco Works]], [[Keith F.C.|Keith]], [[Lossiemouth F.C.|Lossiemouth]], [[Nairn County F.C.|Nairn County]], [[Rothes F.C.|Rothes]], [[Turriff United F.C.|Turriff United]] and [[Wick Academy F.C.|Wick Academy]])\n* Five SFA full member clubs from the [[East of Scotland League]]: ([[Burntisland Shipyard Amateur F.C.|Burntisland Shipyard]], [[Civil Service Strollers F.C.|Civil Service Strollers]], [[Coldstream F.C.|Coldstream]], [[Edinburgh University F.C.|Edinburgh University]], [[Hawick Royal Albert F.C.|Hawick Royal Albert]])\n* Three SFA full member clubs from the [[South of Scotland League]]: ([[Newton Stewart F.C.|Newton Stewart]], [[St Cuthbert Wanderers F.C.|St Cuthbert Wanderers]], [[Wigtown & Bladnoch F.C.|Wigtown & Bladnoch]])\n* Seven SFA full member clubs from the [[Lowland Football League]]: ([[Edinburgh City F.C.|Edinburgh City]], [[Gala Fairydean Rovers F.C.|Gala Fairydean Rovers]], [[Preston Athletic F.C.|Preston Athletic]], [[Selkirk F.C.|Selkirk]], [[Spartans F.C.|Spartans]], [[Threave Rovers F.C.|Threave Rovers]], [[Vale of Leithen F.C.|Vale of Leithen]])\n* Three SFA full member clubs in other leagues: ([[Girvan F.C.|Girvan]], [[Glasgow University F.C.|Glasgow University]], [[Golspie Sutherland F.C.|Golspie Sutherland]])\n* Three qualifiers from the [[Scottish Junior Football Association]]: ([[Auchinleck Talbot F.C.|Auchinleck Talbot]], [[Culter F.C.|Culter]], [[Linlithgow Rose F.C.|Linlithgow Rose]])\n\n{{footballbox collapsible\n|bg=eeeeee\n|date = 14 September 2013\n|time = 15:00\n|team1 = '''[[Edinburgh University F.C.|Edinburgh University]]'''\n|score = 0 \u2013 2\n|report = [http://espnfc.com/uk/en/gamecast/statistics/id/378227/statistics.html?soccernet=true&cc=5739 ESPN]\n|team2 = [[Spartans F.C.|Spartans]]\n|goals1 = \n|goals2 = {{goal|35||43}} Donal Henretty\n|stadium = East Peffermill, [[Edinburgh]]\n|referee = Colin Steven\n|stac