9AnnualReport\"/> \n* [[VDARE Foundation]] (2014, 2015, 2016, 2017, 2018)<ref name=\"whitenation\"/><ref name=\"2015Report\"/><ref name=\"2016Report\"/><ref name=\"WhiteNat2017\"/><ref name=\"2019AnnualReport\"/> \n* Voice of Reason Broadcast Network (2014)<ref name=\"whitenation\"/>\n* [[Washington Summit Publishers]] (2014, 2015, 2016, 2017, 2018)<ref name=\"whitenation\"/><ref name=\"2015Report\"/><ref name=\"2016Report\"/><ref name=\"WhiteNat2017\"/><ref name=\"2019AnnualReport\"/> \n* WeSearchr (2017, 2018)<ref name=\"WhiteNat2017\"/><ref name=\"2019AnnualReport\"/> \n* Western Outlands Supply Company (2017, 2018)<ref name=\"WhiteNat2017\"/><ref name=\"2019AnnualReport\"/> \n* Whitakeronline (2014, 2015)<ref name=\"whitenation\"/><ref name=\"2015Report\"/>\n* White Advocacy Movement (2014, 2015)<ref name=\"whitenation\"/><ref name=\"2015Report\"/>\n* White Boy Society (2014, 2016, 2017, 2018)<ref name=\"whitenation\"/><ref name=\"2016Report\"/><ref name=\"WhiteNat2017\"/><ref name=\"2019AnnualReport\"/> \n* [[White Lives Matter]] (2016)<ref name=\"2016Report\"/>\n* White Man's March (2014)<ref name=\"whitenation\"/>\n* White New York (2016)<ref name=\"2016Report\"/>\n* White Rabbit Radio (2014, 2015, 2016, 2017, 2018)<ref name=\"whitenation\"/><ref name=\"2015Report\"/><ref name=\"2016Report\"/><ref name=\"WhiteNat2017\"/>\n* White Trash Rebel (2015)<ref name=\"2015Report\"/>\n* White Student Union of Tarrant County (2014)<ref name=\"whitenation\"/>\n* White Voice, The (2014, 2015)<ref name=\"whitenation\"/><ref name=\"2015Report\"/>\n* [[Wolves of Vinland]] (2015, 2016)<ref name=\"2015Report\"/><ref name=\"2016Report\"/> \u2013 moved to Neo-V\u00f6lkisch category in 2017<ref name=\"2017NeoVolk\"/>\n* World View Foundations (2014, 2015)<ref name=\"whitenation\"/><ref name=\"2015Report\"/>\n* WTM Enterprises (2014, 2015, 2016)<ref name=\"whitenation\"/><ref name=\"2015Report\"/><ref name=\"2016Report\"/>\n{{div col end}}\n{{clear}}\n\n===Racist skinheads===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"float:right; text-align:center; margin:2em;\"\n|+ Number of racist skinhead hate groups listed over time<ref name=\"2015Report\"/><ref name=\"2016Report\"/><ref name=\"2017Skinheads\">[https://web.archive.org/web/20180408200727/https://www.splcenter.org/fighting-hate/extremist-files/ideology/racist-skinhead 2017 racist skinhead hate groups], Southern Poverty Law Center.</ref><ref name=\"2019AnnualReport\"/>\n! Year\n! Number listed\n|-\n| 2003\n| 39\n|-\n| 2004\n| 48\n|-\n| 2005\n| 56\n|-\n| 2006\n| 78\n|-\n| 2007\n| 90\n|-\n| 2008\n| 98\n|-\n| 2009\n| 122\n|-\n| 2010\n| 136\n|-\n| 2011\n| 133\n|-\n| 2012\n| 138\n|-\n| 2013\n| 126\n|-\n| 2014\n| 119\n|-\n| 2015\n| 95\n|-\n| 2016\n| 78\n|-\n| 2017\n| 71\n|-\n| 2018\n| 63\n|}\n\nThe SPLC defines [[White power skinhead|racist skinhead]] as \"a particularly violent element of the [[white supremacist]] movement,\" often \"referred to as the 'shock troops' of the hoped-for revolution.\"<ref name=\"2019AnnualReport\"/> An offshoot of the [[skinhead]] [[subculture]], racist skinheads promote [[antisemitism]] in addition to white supremacy.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.adl.org/hate_symbols/music.asp|title=White Power Music|accessdate=October 7, 2007|year=2005|publisher=[[Anti-Defamation League]]|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071011040036/http://www.adl.org/hate_symbols/music.asp|archivedate=October 11, 2007|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref name=\"cbsnews.com\">{{cite news|url=http://www.cbsnews.com/stories/2007/02/06/national/main2440306.shtml|publisher=CBS News|title=Immigration Fueling White Supremacists|date=February 6, 2007}}</ref> While racist skinhead groups continue to commit violent acts (against both outsiders and participants in the movement), the number of skinhead groups has declined since 2012, losing ground to \"the racist 'alt-right' and new, younger neo-Nazi and white nationalist groups who are organizing themselves across diffuse social networking sites and platforms.\"<ref name=\"2019AnnualReport\"/>\n\nThe following groups have been listed as active racist skinhead groups in the SPLC's annual reports (years in parentheses refer to the year in which the group is included):\n\n{{div col|colwidth=30em}}\n* AC Skins (2014, 2015, 2016, 2017, 2018)<ref name=\"skinhead\">{{cite web|url=http://www.splcenter.org/get-informed/intelligence-files/ideology/racist-skinhead/active_hate_groups|title=Active Racist Skinhead Groups|publisher=Southern Poverty Law Center|accessdate=July 10, 2014}}</ref><ref name=\"2015Report\"/><ref name=\"2016Report\"/><ref name=\"2017Skinheads\"/><ref name=\"2019AnnualReport\"/>\n* AC/OC (2018)<ref name=\"2019AnnualReport\"/>\n* [[American Front]] (2014, 2015, 2016, 2017, 2018)<ref name=\"skinhead\"/><ref name=\"2015Report\"/><ref name=\"2016Report\"/><ref name=\"2017Skinheads\"/><ref name=\"2019AnnualReport\"/>\n* American Patriot Brigade (2017, 2018)<ref name=\"2017Skinheads\"/><ref name=\"2019AnnualReport\"/>\n* American Vikings (2016, 2017)<ref name=\"2016Report\"/><ref name=\"2017Skinheads\"/>\n* American Viking Clothing Co. (2015, 2018)<ref name=\"2015Report\"/><ref name=\"2019AnnualReport\"/>\n* Aryan Strikeforce (2014, 2015, 2016, 2017)<ref name=\"skinhead\"/><ref name=\"2015Report\"/><ref name=\"2016Report\"/><ref name=\"2017Skinheads\"/>\n* Aryan Terror Brigade (2014, 2015)<ref name=\"skinhead\"/><ref name=\"2015Report\"/>\n* Be Active Front USA (2016, 2017, 2018)<ref name=\"2016Report\"/><ref name=\"2017Skinheads\"/><ref name=\"2019AnnualReport\"/>\n* Bergen County Hooligans (2014)<ref name=\"skinhead\"/>\n* [[Blood & Honour]] U.S.A. (2014, 2015, 2017, 2018) and Blood and Honour America Division (2016, 2017, 2018)<ref name=\"skinhead\"/><ref name=\"2015Report\"/><ref name=\"2016Report\"/><ref name=\"2017Skinheads\"/><ref name=\"2019AnnualReport\"/>\n* Blood and Honour Social Club (2015, 2016, 2017, 2018)<ref name=\"2015Report\"/><ref name=\"2016Report\"/><ref name=\"2017Skinheads\"/><ref name=\"2019AnnualReport\"/>\n* California Skinheads (2015, 2016, 2017, 2018)<ref name=\"2015Report\"/><ref name=\"2016Report\"/><ref name=\"2017Skinheads\"/><ref name=\"2019AnnualReport\"/>\n* Confederate 28 (2017)<ref name=\"2017Skinheads\"/>\n* Confederate Hammerskins (2015, 2016, 2017, 2018)<ref name=\"2015Report\"/><ref name=\"2016Report\"/><ref name=\"2017Skinheads\"/><ref name=\"2019AnnualReport\"/>\n* Crew 38 (2014, 2015, 2016, 2017, 2018)<ref name=\"skinhead\"/><ref name=\"2015Report\"/><ref name=\"2016Report\"/><ref name=\"2017Skinheads\"/><ref name=\"2019AnnualReport\"/>\n* Die Auserwahlten (2014, 2017)<ref name=\"skinhead\"/><ref name=\"2017Skinheads\"/>\n* Eastern Hammerskins (2015, 2016, 2017, 2018)<ref name=\"2015Report\"/><ref name=\"2016Report\"/><ref name=\"2017Skinheads\"/><ref name=\"2019AnnualReport\"/>\n* Firm 22 (2016, 2017)<ref name=\"2016Report\"/><ref name=\"2017Skinheads\"/>\n* Golden State Skinheads (2015, 2016, 2017, 2018)<ref name=\"2015Report\"/><ref name=\"2016Report\"/><ref name=\"2017Skinheads\"/><ref name=\"2019AnnualReport\"/>\n* Golden State Solidarity (2014)<ref name=\"skinhead\"/>\n* Golden-State 45/Kindred 45 (2017)<ref name=\"2017Skinheads\"/>\n* [[Hammerskins]] (2014)<ref name=\"skinhead\"/>\n* Hated and Proud Skins (2014)<ref name=\"skinhead\"/>\n* [[Keystone State Skinheads]] (2014, 2015, 2016, 2018)<ref name=\"skinhead\"/><ref name=\"2015Report\"/><ref name=\"2016Report\"/><ref name=\"2019AnnualReport\"/>\n* [[Keystone United]] (2017)<ref name=\"2017Skinheads\"/>\n* Lone Star United (2014)<ref name=\"skinhead\"/>\n* Maryland State Skinheads (2014, 2015, 2016, 2017)<ref name=\"skinhead\"/><ref name=\"2015Report\"/><ref name=\"2016Report\"/><ref name=\"2017Skinheads\"/>\n* Midland Hammerskins (2015, 2016, 2017, 2018)<ref name=\"2015Report\"/><ref name=\"2016Report\"/><ref name=\"2017Skinheads\"/><ref name=\"2019AnnualReport\"/>\n* Nord Herrenvolk (2014)<ref name=\"skinhead\"/>\n* Northern Hammerskins (2015, 2016, 2017, 2018)<ref name=\"2015Report\"/><ref name=\"2016Report\"/><ref name=\"2017Skinheads\"/><ref name=\"2019AnnualReport\"/>\n* Northwest Hammerskins / Northwestern Hammerskins (2015, 2016, 2017, 2018)<ref name=\"2015Report\"/><ref name=\"2016Report\"/><ref name=\"2017Skinheads\"/><ref name=\"2019AnnualReport\"/>\n* Old Glory Skinheads (2014, 2015)<ref name=\"skinhead\"/><ref name=\"2015Report\"/>\n* Orange County Skins (2014)<ref name=\"skinhead\"/>\n* Sacto Skins/Sacto Skinheads (2014, 2015, 2016, 2017, 2018)<ref name=\"skinhead\"/><ref name=\"2015Report\"/><ref name=\"2016Report\"/><ref name=\"2017Skinheads\"/><ref name=\"2019AnnualReport\"/>\n* [[Sadistic Souls Motorcycle Club|Sadistic Souls Skinheads]]<ref name=\"2015Report\"/>\n* Supreme White Alliance (2014, 2015, 2016)<ref name=\"skinhead\"/><ref name=\"2015Report\"/><ref name=\"2016Report\"/>\n* The Hated (2014, 2015)<ref name=\"skinhead\"/><ref name=\"2015Report\"/>\n* United Society of Aryan Skinheads (2014)<ref name=\"skinhead\"/>\n* United Southern Skins (2018)<ref name=\"2019AnnualReport\"/>\n* Vinland Clothing (2016)<ref name=\"2016Report\"/>\n* Vinlanders / Vinlanders Social Club (2014, 2015, 2016, 2017, 2018)<ref name=\"skinhead\"/><ref name=\"2015Report\"/><ref name=\"2016Report\"/><ref name=\"2017Skinheads\"/><ref name=\"2019AnnualReport\"/>\n* Warlord Skins (2015)<ref name=\"2015Report\"/>\n* Warrior's Pride Clothing (2017, 2018)<ref name=\"2017Skinheads\"/><ref name=\"2019AnnualReport\"/>\n* Western Hammerskins (2015, 2016, 2017, 2018)<ref name=\"2015Report\"/><ref name=\"2016Report\"/><ref name=\"2017Skinheads\"/><ref name=\"2019AnnualReport\"/>\n{{div col end}}\n{{clear}}\n\n===Extreme antigovernment movement===\n{{see also|List of militia organizations in the United States}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"float:right; text-align:center; margin:2em;\"\n|+ Number of extreme antigovernment groups over time<ref name=\"2019AnnualReport\"/>\n! Year\n! Number listed\n|-\n| 2014\n| 874\n|-\n| 2015\n| 998\n|-\n| 2016\n| 623\n|-\n| 2017\n| 689\n|-\n| 2018\n| 612\n|}\nIn 2018, the SPLC identified 612 groups that belonged to the extreme antigovernment movement; about a quarter of these were part of the [[militia movement]].<ref name=\"2019AnnualReport\"/> A subset within this movement is the [[sovereign citizen movement|\"sovereign citizen\" movement]]. The SPLC states that \"Generally, antigovernment groups define themselves as opposed to the '[[New World Order (conspiracy theory)|New World Order]], engage in groundless conspiracy theorizing, or advocate or adhere to extreme antigovernment doctrines. Antigovernment groups do not necessarily advocate or engage in violence or other criminal activities, though some have. Many warn of impending government violence or the need to prepare for a coming revolution. Many antigovernment groups are not racist.\"<ref name=\"Antigov\">[https://web.archive.org/web/20180408210912/https://www.splcenter.org/fighting-hate/extremist-files/ideology/antigovernment Antigoverment Movement], Southern Poverty Law Center.</ref>\n\nThe SPLC has listed a number of antigovernment groups, including [[Oath Keepers]], various [[3 Percenters]] groups (also styled III%ers), the [[John Birch Society]], Renew America, the [[Moorish Science Temple of America#Twenty-first century|Moorish Science Temple of America 1928]].<ref name=\"Antigov\"/><ref name=\"2019AnnualReport\"/>\n\n===Black separatist/nationalist===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"float:right; text-align:center; margin:2em;\"\n|+ Number of black separatist hate groups listed over time<ref name=\"2015Report\"/><ref name=\"2016Report\"/><ref name=\"2017BlackNationalist\"/><ref name=\"2019AnnualReport\"/>\n! Year\n! Number listed\n|-\n| 2003\n| 136\n|-\n| 2004\n| 108\n|-\n| 2005\n| 106\n|-\n| 2006\n| 88\n|-\n| 2007\n| 81\n|-\n| 2008\n| 112\n|-\n| 2009\n| 121\n|-\n| 2010\n| 149\n|-\n| 2011\n| 140\n|-\n| 2012\n| 151\n|-\n| 2013\n| 115\n|-\n| 2014\n| 113\n|-\n| 2015\n| 180\n|-\n| 2016\n| 193\n|-\n| 2017\n| 233\n|-\n| 2018\n| 264\n|}\nBlack nationalist groups espouse [[black separatism]], a movement seeking to create separate institutions for [[black people]]. The SPLC notes: \"Most forms of black nationalism are strongly anti-white, antisemitic and anti-LGBT. Some religious versions assert that black people are the biblical 'chosen people' of God.\"<ref name=\"2019AnnualReport\"/> The following groups have been listed as active black separatist groups in the SPLC's annual reports (years in parentheses refer to the year in which the group is included):\n\n* All Eyes on Egypt Bookstore or All Eyes on Egipt Bookstore \u2013 see [[Nuwaubian Nation]] (2014, 2015, 2016, 2017, 2018)<ref name=\"separatist\">{{cite web|url=http://www.splcenter.org/get-informed/intelligence-files/ideology/black-separatist/active_hate_groups|title=Active Black Separatist Groups|publisher=Southern Poverty Law Center|accessdate=July 9, 2014}}</ref><ref name=\"2015Report\"/><ref name=\"2016Report\"/><ref name=\"2017BlackNationalist\">[https://web.archive.org/web/20180310122353/https://www.splcenter.org/fighting-hate/extremist-files/ideology/black-nationalist 2017 black nationalist hate groups], Southern Poverty Law Center.</ref><ref name=\"2019AnnualReport\"/>\n* Ambassadors of Christ (2017, 2018)<ref name=\"2017BlackNationalist\"/><ref name=\"2019AnnualReport\"/>\n* Ancient Egyptian Distribution Company (2017, 2018)<ref name=\"2017BlackNationalist\"/><ref name=\"2019AnnualReport\"/>\n* Army of Israel (2017, 2018)<ref name=\"2017BlackNationalist\"/><ref name=\"2019AnnualReport\"/>\n* Black Hebrew Israelites (2015)<ref name=\"2015Report\"/>\n* [[Black Riders Liberation Party]] (2014, 2015, 2016, 2017, 2018)<ref name=\"separatist\"/><ref name=\"2015Report\"/><ref name=\"2016Report\"/><ref name=\"2017BlackNationalist\"/><ref name=\"2019AnnualReport\"/>\n* Great Millstone (2017, 2018)<ref name=\"2017BlackNationalist\"/><ref name=\"2019AnnualReport\"/>\n* House of David/House of David Camp (2017, 2018)<ref name=\"2017BlackNationalist\"/><ref name=\"2019AnnualReport\"/>\n* House of Israel (2017, 2018)<ref name=\"2017BlackNationalist\"/><ref name=\"2019AnnualReport\"/>\n* International Society of Indigenous Sovereigns (2018)<ref name=\"2019AnnualReport\"/>\n* Israel United In Christ (2015, 2016, 2017, 2018)<ref name=\"2015Report\"/><ref name=\"2016Report\"/><ref name=\"2017BlackNationalist\"/><ref name=\"2019AnnualReport\"/>\n* [[Israelite Church of God in Jesus Christ]], The (2014, 2015, 2016, 2017, 2018)<ref name=\"separatist\"/><ref name=\"2015Report\"/><ref name=\"2016Report\"/><ref name=\"2017BlackNationalist\"/><ref name=\"2019AnnualReport\"/>\n* [[Israelite School of Universal Practical Knowledge]] (2015, 2016, 2017, 2018)<ref name=\"2015Report\"/><ref name=\"2016Report\"/><ref name=\"2017BlackNationalist\"/><ref name=\"2019AnnualReport\"/>\n* Israelite the Branches (2018)<ref name=\"2019AnnualReport\"/>\n* Israelite Saints of Christ (2018)<ref name=\"2019AnnualReport\"/>\n* Lion of Judah - Jeshurun Lions (2018)<ref name=\"2019AnnualReport\"/>\n* Lions of Israel (2017)<ref name=\"2017BlackNationalist\"/><ref name=\"2019AnnualReport\"/>\n* Luxor Couture (2018)<ref name=\"2019AnnualReport\"/>\n* Masharah Yasharahla (2018)<ref name=\"2019AnnualReport\"/>\n* Mountains of Israel (2018)<ref name=\"2019AnnualReport\"/>\n* National Black Foot Soldier Network (2014)<ref name=\"separatist\"/>\n* [[Nation of Islam]] (2014, 2015, 2016, 2017, 2018)<ref name=\"separatist\"/><ref name=\"2015Report\"/><ref name=\"2016Report\"/><ref name=\"2017BlackNationalist\"/><ref name=\"2019AnnualReport\"/>\n* Nation of Kings and Priests (2017, 2018)<ref name=\"2017BlackNationalist\"/><ref name=\"2019AnnualReport\"/>\n* New Black Liberation Militia (2018)<ref name=\"2019AnnualReport\"/>\n* [[New Black Panther Party]] (2014, 2015, 2016, 2017, 2018)<ref name=\"separatist\"/><ref name=\"2015Report\"/><ref name=\"2016Report\"/><ref name=\"2017BlackNationalist\"/><ref name=\"2019AnnualReport\"/>\n* New Black Panther Party for Self Defense (2016, 2017, 2018)<ref name=\"2016Report\"/><ref name=\"2017BlackNationalist\"/><ref name=\"2019AnnualReport\"/>\n* Northern Kingdom Prophets (2018)<ref name=\"2019AnnualReport\"/>\n* OneBody in Yahawashi (2017, 2018)<ref name=\"2017BlackNationalist\"/><ref name=\"2019AnnualReport\"/>\n* Revolutionary Black Panther Party (2018)<ref name=\"2019AnnualReport\"/>\n* Sicarii 1715 (2016, 2017, 2018)<ref name=\"2016Report\"/><ref name=\"2017BlackNationalist\"/><ref name=\"2019AnnualReport\"/>\n* True Nation Israelite Congregation (2018)<ref name=\"2019AnnualReport\"/>\n* Trumpet in Philly (2018)<ref name=\"2019AnnualReport\"/>\n* United Kingdom of Israel Congregation (2017, 2018)<ref name=\"2017BlackNationalist\"/><ref name=\"2019AnnualReport\"/>\n* United Nuwaubian Nation of Moors/All Eyes on Egipt (2017, 2018)<ref name=\"2017BlackNationalist\"/><ref name=\"2019AnnualReport\"/>\n* War On The Horizon (2014, 2015, 2016, 2017, 2018)<ref name=\"separatist\"/><ref name=\"2015Report\"/><ref name=\"2017BlackNationalist\"/><ref name=\"2016Report\"/>\n* Watchmen of Israel (2018)<ref name=\"2019AnnualReport\"/>\n{{clear}}\n\n===Neo-Confederate===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"float:right; text-align:center; margin:2em;\"\n|+ Number of neo-Confederate hate groups listed over time<ref name=\"2015Report\"/><ref name=\"2016Report\"/><ref name=\"2017NeoConfed\">[https://web.archive.org/web/20180408200831/https://www.splcenter.org/fighting-hate/extremist-files/ideology/neo-confederate 2017 neo-Confederate hate groups], Southern Poverty Law Center.</ref><ref name=\"2019AnnualReport\"/>\n! Year\n! Number listed\n|-\n| 2003\n| 91\n|-\n| 2004\n| 97\n|-\n| 2005\n| 99\n|-\n| 2006\n| 102\n|-\n| 2007\n| 104\n|-\n| 2008\n| 93\n|-\n| 2009\n| 68\n|-\n| 2010\n| 42\n|-\n| 2011\n| 32\n|-\n| 2012\n| 30\n|-\n| 2013\n| 36\n|-\n| 2014\n| 37\n|-\n| 2015\n| 35\n|-\n| 2016\n| 43\n|-\n| 2017\n| 31\n|-\n| 2018\n| 36\n|}\nThe SPLC classifies [[neo-Confederate]] groups as those with \"a reactionary, revisionist predilection for symbols of the [[Confederate States of America]], typically paired with a strong belief in the validity of the failed doctrines of [[Nullification (U.S. Constitution)|nullification]] and [[Secession in the United States|secession]] \u2014 in the specific context of the antebellum South.\"<ref name=\"2017NeoConfed\"/>\n\nThe following groups have been listed as active neo-Confederate groups in the SPLC's annual reports (years in parentheses refer to the year in which the group is included):\n* ACTBAC NC (2016, 2017)<ref name=\"2016Report\"/><ref name=\"2017NeoConfed\"/>\n* Dixie Republic (2014, 2015, 2016, 2017, 2018)<ref name=\"neocon\">{{cite web|url=http://www.splcenter.org/get-informed/intelligence-files/ideology/neo-confederate/active_hate_groups|title=Active Neo-Confederate Groups|publisher=Southern Poverty Law Center|accessdate=July 10, 2014}}</ref><ref name=\"2015Report\"/><ref name=\"2016Report\"/><ref name=\"2017NeoConfed\"/><ref name=\"2019AnnualReport\"/>\n* FreeMississippi (2016)<ref name=\"2016Report\"/>\n* Identity Dixie (2017, 2018)<ref name=\"2017NeoConfed\"/><ref name=\"2019AnnualReport\"/>\n* Kingdom Treasure Ministries (2014, 2015)<ref name=\"neocon\"/><ref name=\"2015Report\"/>\n* [[League of the South]] (2014, 2015, 2016, 2017, 2018)<ref name=\"neocon\"/><ref name=\"2015Report\"/><ref name=\"2016Report\"/><ref name=\"2017NeoConfed\"/><ref name=\"2019AnnualReport\"/>\n* Livin' the Legacy (2014)<ref name=\"neocon\"/>\n* Mary Noel Kershaw Foundation (2014, 2015, 2016, 2017)<ref name=\"neocon\"/><ref name=\"2015Report\"/><ref name=\"2016Report\"/><ref name=\"2017NeoConfed\"/>\n* Pace Confederate Depot (2014, 2015, 2016, 2017)<ref name=\"neocon\"/><ref name=\"2015Report\"/><ref name=\"2016Report\"/><ref name=\"2017NeoConfed\"/>\n* Southern Culture Center (2014)<ref name=\"neocon\"/>\n* Southern Future (2016, 2017)<ref name=\"2016Report\"/><ref name=\"2017NeoConfed\"/>\n* Southern National Congress (2014, 2015, 2016)<ref name=\"neocon\"/><ref name=\"2015Report\"/><ref name=\"2016Report\"/>\n* Southern Nationalist Network (2015)<ref name=\"2015Report\"/>\n* Southern Patriot Shoppe (2015)<ref name=\"2015Report\"/>\n* Southern Revivalist (2018)<ref name=\"2019AnnualReport\"/>\n* Wildman's Civil War Surplus and Herb Shop (2018)<ref name=\"2019AnnualReport\"/>\n{{clear}}\n\n===Christian Identity===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"float:right; text-align:center; margin:2em;\"\n|+ Number of Christian Identity hate groups listed over time<ref name=\"2015Report\"/><ref name=\"2016Report\"/><ref name=\"2017ChristianIdentity\">[https://web.archive.org/web/20180408210031/https://www.splcenter.org/fighting-hate/extremist-files/ideology/christian-identity 2017 Christian identity hate groups], Southern Poverty Law Center.</ref><ref name=\"2019AnnualReport\"/>\n! Year\n! Number listed\n|-\n| 2003\n| 31\n|-\n| 2004\n| 28\n|-\n| 2005\n| 35\n|-\n| 2006\n| 37\n|-\n| 2007\n| 36\n|-\n| 2008\n| 39\n|-\n| 2009\n| 37\n|-\n| 2010\n| 26\n|-\n| 2011\n| 55\n|-\n| 2012\n| 54\n|-\n| 2013\n| 37\n|-\n| 2014\n| 21\n|-\n| 2015\n| 19\n|-\n| 2016\n| 21\n|-\n| 2017\n| 20\n|-\n| 2018\n| 17\n|}\n[[Christian Identity]] is a label applied to a wide variety of loosely affiliated believers and [[church (building)|churches]] with a [[white supremacy|white supremacist]] and [[Anti-Semitism|antisemitic]] theology that claims that [[White people]] are the true descendants of the [[Lost Tribes of Israel]].<ref>For background see:\n* {{cite book|last=Eck|first=Diane|year=2001|authorlink=Diana L. Eck|title=A New Religious America: How a \"Christian Country\" has become the world's most religiously diverse nation|url=https://archive.org/details/newreligiousamer00eckd|url-access=registration|location=New York|publisher=HarperCollins Publishers|page=[https://archive.org/details/newreligiousamer00eckd/page/347 347]}}\n* {{cite book|last=Buck|first=Christopher|title=Religious Myths and Visions of America: How Minority Faiths Redefined America's World Role|year=2009|publisher=Praeger|isbn=978-0313359590|pages=107\u201308, 213}}\n* {{cite web|url=http://www.adl.org/learn/ext_us/Christian_Identity.asp?xpicked=4&item=Christian_ID |title=Christian Identity |publisher=Adl.org |accessdate=January 24, 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120119052722/http://www.adl.org/learn/ext_us/Christian_Identity.asp?xpicked=4&item=Christian_ID |archivedate=January 19, 2012 }}\n* {{cite book|last=Barkun|first=Michael|author-link=Michael Barkun|year=1996|title=Religion and the Racist Right: The Origins of the Christian Identity Movement|pages=x, xii, xiii|chapter=preface|publisher=University of North Carolina Press|isbn=0807823287}}</ref>\n\nThe following groups have been listed as Christian Identity hate groups in the SPLC's annual reports (years in parentheses refer to the year in which the group is included):\n{{div col|colwidth=30em}}\n* [[11th Hour Remnant Messenger]] (2014)<ref name=\"christianID\">{{cite web|url=http://www.splcenter.org/get-informed/intelligence-files/ideology/christian-identity/active_hate_groups|title=Active Christian Identity Groups|publisher=Southern Poverty Law Center|accessdate=July 9, 2014}}</ref>\n* America's Promise Ministries (2014, 2015, 2016, 2017, 2018)<ref name=\"christianID\"/><ref name=\"2015Report\"/><ref name=\"2016Report\"/><ref name=\"2017ChristianIdentity\"/><ref name=\"2019AnnualReport\"/>\n* Christian American Ministries (2016, 2017, 2018)<ref name=\"2016Report\"/><ref name=\"2017ChristianIdentity\"/><ref name=\"2019AnnualReport\"/>\n* Christian Identity Church \u2013 Aryan Nations (2014)<ref name=\"christianID\"/>\n* Christian Revival Center (2015, 2016, 2017, 2018)<ref name=\"2015Report\"/><ref name=\"2016Report\"/><ref name=\"2017ChristianIdentity\"/><ref name=\"2019AnnualReport\"/>\n* Church of Israel (2016, 2017, 2018)<ref name=\"2016Report\"/><ref name=\"2017ChristianIdentity\"/><ref name=\"2019AnnualReport\"/