ction (2014, 2015, 2016, 2017, 2018)<ref name=\"2015Report\"/><ref name=\"2016Report\"/><ref name=\"2017RadicalTrad\"/><ref name=\"2019AnnualReport\"/>\n{{div col end}}\n{{clear}}\n\n===Anti-Muslim===\nAnti-[[Muslim]] hate groups are described by the SPLC as groups which [[Islamophobia|exhibit extreme hostility against Muslims]], by depicting Muslims as \"fundamentally alien, ... irrational, intolerant and violent\" and accusing Islam of \"sanctioning [[pedophilia]], coupled with [[LGBT in Islam|intolerance for homosexuals]] and [[Women in Islam|women]].\"<ref name=\"IntelligenceFilesIdeologyAntiMuslim\">{{cite web|url=http://www.splcenter.org/get-informed/intelligence-files/ideology/anti-muslim |title=Anti-Muslim|publisher=Southern Poverty Law Center}}</ref> Anti-Muslim hate groups espouse conspiratorial views of American Muslims, viewing them \"as a [[fifth column]] intent on undermining and eventually replacing American democracy and Western civilization with Islamic despotism, a [[Counter-jihad|conspiracy theory known as 'civilization jihad]].'\"<ref name=\"IntelligenceFilesIdeologyAntiMuslim\"/> The following groups have been listed as anti-Muslim hate groups in the SPLC's annual reports (years in parentheses refer to the year in which the group is included):\n\n{{div col|colwidth=30em}}\n* III% Security Force (2016)<ref name=\"2016Report\"/>\n* [[ACT! for America]] (2015, 2016, 2017, 2018)<ref name=\"2015Report\"/><ref name=\"2016Report\"/><ref name=\"2017AntiMuslim\">[https://web.archive.org/web/20180408203615/https://www.splcenter.org/fighting-hate/extremist-files/ideology/anti-muslim 2017 anti-Muslim hate groups], Southern Poverty Law Center.</ref><ref name=\"2019AnnualReport\"/>\n* Altra Firearms (2016)<ref name=\"2016Report\"/>\n* American Constitution Center (2016)<ref name=\"2016Report\"/>\n* American Defence League (2014, 2015)<ref name=\"muslim\">{{cite web|url=http://www.splcenter.org/node/3502/activegroups|title=Active Anti-Muslim Groups|publisher=Southern Poverty Law Center|work=Intelligence Report|date=Spring 2015}}</ref><ref name=\"2015Report\"/>\n* American Freedom Alliance (2016, 2017, 2018)<ref name=\"2016Report\"/><ref name=\"2017AntiMuslim\"/><ref name=\"2019AnnualReport\"/>\n* [[American Freedom Defense Initiative]] (also known as [[Freedom Defense Initiative]] and [[Stop Islamization of America]]) (2014, 2015, 2016, 2017, 2018)<ref name=\"muslim\"/><ref name=\"2015Report\"/><ref name=\"2016Report\"/><ref name=\"2017AntiMuslim\"/><ref name=\"2019AnnualReport\"/>\n* [[American Freedom Law Center]] (2015, 2016, 2017, 2018)<ref name=\"2015Report\"/><ref name=\"2016Report\"/><ref name=\"2017AntiMuslim\"/><ref name=\"2019AnnualReport\"/>\n* American Public Policy Alliance (2017, 2018)<ref name=\"2017AntiMuslim\"/><ref name=\"2019AnnualReport\"/>\n* American Security Rally of Montana (2016, 2017)<ref name=\"2016Report\"/><ref name=\"2017AntiMuslim\"/>\n* Americans for America (2017)<ref name=\"2017AntiMuslim\"/>\n* [[Atlas Shrugs]] (2014, 2015)<ref name=\"muslim\"/><ref name=\"2015Report\"/>\n* Bare Naked Islam (2014, 2015, 2016)<ref name=\"muslim\"/><ref name=\"2015Report\"/><ref name=\"2016Report\"/>\n* [[Bomb Islam]], operated by [[Robert Sterkeson]] (2016, 2017, 2018)<ref name=\"2016Report\"/><ref name=\"2017AntiMuslim\"/><ref name=\"2019AnnualReport\"/><ref name=\"medi_Self\">{{Cite web |title=Self-proclaimed Nazi who says he flew a swastika flag at a Bernie Sanders rally still has a YouTube account |author= |work=Media Matters for America |date= |access-date=11 March 2020 |url= https://www.mediamatters.org/white-nationalism/self-proclaimed-nazi-who-says-he-flew-swastika-flag-bernie-sanders-rally-still |quote=This would not be the first time Sterkeson \u2014 who also goes by his handle \u201cBomb Islam\u201d \u2014 has spewed bigotry at a public event. In 2017, a fellow vlogger filmed Sterkeson yelling anti-Islam sentiments at a Council on American-Islamic Relations event featuring Women\u2019s March co-founder Linda Sarsour in Mesa, Arizona. In the video, Sterkeson approached people with professional cameras and began shouting about his belief that \u201cevery single one of them has to go.\u201d Later in the video, a man in a Pepe the frog mask goes inside the lobby of the event hosted at a hotel and tears up a Quran while the person holding the camera calls the Muslims assembled there \u201cbearded monkeys,\u201d saying they have \u201cno place in America.\u201d }}</ref>\n* Bureau on American Islamic Relations (2015, 2016, 2017, 2018)<ref name=\"2015Report\"/><ref name=\"2017AntiMuslim\"/><ref name=\"2019AnnualReport\"/>\n* Casa D'Ice Signs (2014, 2015)<ref name=\"muslim\"/><ref name=\"2015Report\"/>\n* [[Center for Security Policy]] (2015, 2016, 2017, 2018)<ref name=\"2015Report\"/><ref name=\"2016Report\"/><ref name=\"2017AntiMuslim\"/><ref name=\"2019AnnualReport\"/>\n* [[Christian Action Network]]  (2014, 2015, 2016, 2017, 2018)<ref name=\"muslim\"/><ref name=\"2015Report\"/><ref name=\"2016Report\"/><ref name=\"2017AntiMuslim\"/><ref name=\"2019AnnualReport\"/>\n* Christian Guardians (2014, 2015)<ref name=\"muslim\"/><ref name=\"2015Report\"/>\n* [[Christian Phalange]] (2014)<ref name=\"muslim\"/>\n* Christians and Jews United for Israel (Hillsborough, New Hampshire) (2017)<ref name=\"2017AntiMuslim\"/>\n* Citizens' Action Group of South Florida (2017, 2018)<ref name=\"2017AntiMuslim\"/><ref name=\"2019AnnualReport\"/>\n* Citizens for National Security (2014, 2015, 2016, 2017, 2018)<ref name=\"muslim\"/><ref name=\"2015Report\"/><ref name=\"2016Report\"/><ref name=\"2017AntiMuslim\"/><ref name=\"2019AnnualReport\"/>\n* Citizens for the St. Croix Valley (2017, 2018)<ref name=\"2017AntiMuslim\"/><ref name=\"2019AnnualReport\"/>\n* Citizen Warrior (2014, 2015)<ref name=\"muslim\"/><ref name=\"2015Report\"/><ref name=\"2016Report\"/>\n* [[Clarion Project]] (2016, 2017, 2018)<ref name=\"2016Report\"/><ref name=\"2017AntiMuslim\"/><ref name=\"2019AnnualReport\"/