{"title_page": "Madness (All That Remains album)", "text_new": "{{Infobox album\n| name       = Madness\n| type       = Studio\n| artist     = [[All That Remains (band)|All That Remains]]\n| cover      = ATRMadness.jpg\n| alt        =\n| released   = April 28, 2017\n| recorded   = 2016\n| venue      =\n| studio     = West Valley Studios, [[Woodland Hills, California]], U.S.\n| genre      = {{hlist|[[Alternative metal]]|[[melodic metalcore]]}}\n| length     = 50:17\n| label      = {{hlist|[[Razor & Tie]]|[[Concord Bicycle Music]]}}\n| producer   = [[Howard Benson]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.blabbermouth.net/news/all-that-remains-listen-to-two-new-songs-madness-and-safe-house/|title=All That Remains: Listen To Two New Songs 'Madness' And 'Safe House'|work=Blabbermouth.net |date=February 2, 2017|accessdate=February 20, 2017}}</ref>\n| prev_title = [[The Order of Things (album)|The Order of Things]]\n| prev_year  = 2015\n| next_title = [[Victim of the New Disease]]\n| next_year  = 2018\n| misc       = {{Singles\n | name        = Madness\n | type        = Studio\n | single1     = Madness\n | single1date = February 3, 2017\n | single2     = Safe House\n | single2date = February 3, 2017\n | single3     = Halo\n | single3date = March 24, 2017\n | single4     = Louder\n | single4date = April 13, 2017\n | single5     = [[The Thunder Rolls#All That Remains cover version|The Thunder Rolls]]\n | single5date = August 22, 2017\n}}\n}}\n\n'''''Madness''''' is the eighth studio album by [[All That Remains (band)|All That Remains]]. It was released on April 28, 2017,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://loudwire.com/all-that-remains-madness-exclusive-lyric-video-premiere/ |title=All That Remains, 'Madness' \u2013 Exclusive Lyric Video Premiere |work=Loudwire |date=February 27, 2017 |accessdate=March 5, 2017 |author=Childers, Chad}}</ref> on [[Razor & Tie]] Records. ''Madness'' is the first studio album produced by [[Howard Benson]], as well as the first album to feature bassist Aaron Patrick. While this is the band's next-to-last album with guitarist Oli Herbert, it is also their last album to be released in his lifetime.\n\n==Background==\nVocalist [[Phil Labonte]] told ''[[Revolver (magazine)|Revolver]]'' magazine about band's approach on the new disc: \"We wanted to mix it up a little bit and write from a vocal perspective this time. So I went to L.A. and came up with vocal ideas and melodies and then sent those chord progressions back to Oli Herbert and he wrote riffs in response to that. Doing it this way turned the record into a vocal album as opposed to a guitar album. And that affected some things. Like, there might be less intricacy in the riffs because they were written in response to my voice.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.blabbermouth.net/news/all-that-remains-announces-madness-u-s-tour/|title=ALL THAT REMAINS Announces 'Madness' U.S. Tour|work=blabbermouth.net|date=March 14, 2017|accessdate=January 18, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Musical style==\nLabonte added that the majority of the new songs features \"significant programming and electronic sounds. And that's something we wanted to have flowing through the entire record. So you're gonna hear that kind of influence on most of the tracks.\" <ref name=\"blabbermouth.net\">{{cite web|url=http://www.blabbermouth.net/news/all-that-remains-singer-responds-to-sellout-accusations-says-there-is-plenty-of-heavy-material-on-upcoming-album/|title=ALL THAT REMAINS Singer Responds To 'Sellout' Accusations, Says There Is Plenty Of Heavy Material On Upcoming Album|work=blabbermouth.net|date=February 22, 2017|accessdate=January 18, 2018}}</ref>\n\nPhil also stated: \"On this record, there's five songs on the record that are exactly what you would expect from ''All That Remains''. There's some songs where we kind of were, like, 'All right, let's push this and maybe change what we can do, or what ''All That Remains'' is allowed to do.' But it ain't like we're not heavy anymore. And if you're just, like, 'Oh, they're not heavy anymore,' then you're just not listening.\"<ref name=\"blabbermouth.net\"/>\n\n==Reception==\nThe album received mixed reviews. Aaron J. Marko of ''[[Exclaim!]]'' described the album as mediocre, generic and archaic.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://exclaim.ca/music/article/all_that_remains-madness|title=All That Remains Madness|website=exclaim.ca|accessdate=January 18, 2018}}</ref> Christopher Di Carlo of Overdrive magazine,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://overdrive-mag.com/2017/05/30/album-review-all-that-remains-madness/|title=Album Review: All That Remains \u2013 Madness \u2013 Overdrive Music Magazine|work=Overdrive|date=May 30, 2017|accessdate=January 18, 2018}}</ref> on the other hand, described the album as beautiful yet heavy.\n\n==Track listing==\nAll lyrics written by Phil Labonte; all music composed by All That Remains.\n\n{{Track listing\n|title1 = Safe House\n|length1 = 3:37\n|title2 = Madness\n|length2 = 3:24\n|title3 = Nothing I Can Do\n|length3 = 3:41\n|title4 = If I'm Honest\n|length4 = 4:25\n|title5 = Halo\n|length5 = 4:03\n|title6 = Louder\n|length6 = 3:11\n|title7 = Rivercity\n|length7 = 5:33\n|title8 = Open Grave\n|length8 = 3:42\n|title9 = Far from Home\n|length9 = 4:05\n|title10 = Trust and Believe\n|length10 = 3:14\n|title11 = Back to You\n|length11 = 3:25\n|title12 = Never Sorry\n|length12 = 3:37\n|title13 = [[The Thunder Rolls#All That Remains cover version|The Thunder Rolls]]\n|note13 = [[Garth Brooks]] cover\n|length13 = 4:22\n|total_length = 50:17\n}}\n\n==Personnel==\n===All That Remains===\n* [[Philip Labonte]] \u2013 [[Lead vocalist|lead vocals]], art direction, cover design\n* Oli Herbert \u2013 [[lead guitar]]\n* Mike Martin \u2013 [[rhythm guitar]]\n* Aaron Patrick \u2013 [[bass guitar]], backing vocals\n* [[Jason Costa]] \u2013 [[Drum kit|drums]]\n\n===Additional musicians===\n*Mark Sereikas - additional guitar on \"Thunder Rolls\"\n*Benny Goodman - piano/keyboards and additional engineering/production on Thunder Rolls at Speak EZ Studios, Randolph, MA\n*Cory Paza - bass and additional engineering/production on Thunder rolls at Speak EZ Studios, Randolph, MA\n\n====Freedom Chorus====\n*[[Diamante (musician)|Diamante]] (also does additional vocals on \"Thunder Rolls\")\n*Meron Ryan\n*Sidnie Tipton\n*Lenny Skolnik\n*Seann Bowe\n\n===Production===\n* [[Howard Benson]] \u2013 production, mixing\n* Mike Plotnikoff \u2013 co-production, engineering\n* Hatsukazu \"Hatch\" Inagaki \u2013 engineering\n* Shaun Ezrol and Carl Stoodt \u2013 assistant engineering\n* [[Bob Ludwig]] \u2013 mastering \n* Lenny Skolnik, Seann Bowe, Howard Benson \u2013 keyboards and programming\n* Marc VanGool \u2013 guitar tech\n* Jon Nicholson at Drum Fetish \u2013 drum tech\n* Joe Rickard \u2013 pre-production, drum programming\n* Igor Khoroshev \u2013 string arrangement on \"Back to You\"\n* Paul DeCarli \u2013 digital editing\n* Nick Haussling \u2013 A&R\n* Tom Gnolfo \u2013 A&R administration\n* Diamante Azzura \u2013 backing vocals\n* [[The White Noise|Josh Strock]] \u2013 composition<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.allmusic.com/artist/josh-strock-mn0003478209|title=Josh Strock \u2013 Credits \u2013 AllMusic|website=AllMusic|accessdate=January 18, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Charts==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Chart (2017)\n! scope=\"col\"| Peak<br /> position\n|-\n{{album chart|BillboardCanada|77|artist=All That Remains|rowheader=true|accessdate=May 9, 2017}}\n|-\n{{album chart|Billboard200|50|artist=All That Remains|rowheader=true|accessdate=May 9, 2017}}\n|-\n{{album chart|BillboardRock|9|artist=All That Remains|rowheader=true|accessdate=May 9, 2017}}\n|-\n{{album chart|BillboardHardRock|1|artist=All That Remains|rowheader=true|accessdate=May 20, 2017}}\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n{{All That Remains}}\n\n[[Category:2017 albums]]\n[[Category:All That Remains (band) albums]]\n[[Category:Razor & Tie albums]]\n[[Category:Albums produced by Howard Benson]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox album\n| name       = Madness\n| type       = Studio\n| artist     = [[All That Remains (band)|All That Remains]]\n| cover      = ATRMadness.jpg\n| alt        =\n| released   = April 28, 2017\n| recorded   = 2016\n| venue      =\n| studio     = West Valley Studios, [[Woodland Hills, California]], U.S.\n| genre      = {{hlist|[[Alternative metal]]|[[hard rock]]|[[metalcore]]}}\n| length     = 50:17\n| label      = {{hlist|[[Razor & Tie]]|[[Concord Bicycle Music]]}}\n| producer   = [[Howard Benson]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.blabbermouth.net/news/all-that-remains-listen-to-two-new-songs-madness-and-safe-house/|title=All That Remains: Listen To Two New Songs 'Madness' And 'Safe House'|work=Blabbermouth.net |date=February 2, 2017|accessdate=February 20, 2017}}</ref>\n| prev_title = [[The Order of Things (album)|The Order of Things]]\n| prev_year  = 2015\n| next_title = [[Victim of the New Disease]]\n| next_year  = 2018\n| misc       = {{Singles\n | name        = Madness\n | type        = Studio\n | single1     = Madness\n | single1date = February 3, 2017\n | single2     = Safe House\n | single2date = February 3, 2017\n | single3     = Halo\n | single3date = March 24, 2017\n | single4     = Louder\n | single4date = April 13, 2017\n | single5     = [[The Thunder Rolls#All That Remains cover version|The Thunder Rolls]]\n | single5date = August 22, 2017\n}}\n}}\n\n'''''Madness''''' is the eighth studio album by [[All That Remains (band)|All That Remains]]. It was released on April 28, 2017,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://loudwire.com/all-that-remains-madness-exclusive-lyric-video-premiere/ |title=All That Remains, 'Madness' \u2013 Exclusive Lyric Video Premiere |work=Loudwire |date=February 27, 2017 |accessdate=March 5, 2017 |author=Childers, Chad}}</ref> on [[Razor & Tie]] Records. ''Madness'' is the first studio album produced by [[Howard Benson]], as well as the first album to feature bassist Aaron Patrick. While this is the band's next-to-last album with guitarist Oli Herbert, it is also their last album to be released in his lifetime.\n\n==Background==\nVocalist [[Phil Labonte]] told ''[[Revolver (magazine)|Revolver]]'' magazine about band's approach on the new disc: \"We wanted to mix it up a little bit and write from a vocal perspective this time. So I went to L.A. and came up with vocal ideas and melodies and then sent those chord progressions back to Oli Herbert and he wrote riffs in response to that. Doing it this way turned the record into a vocal album as opposed to a guitar album. And that affected some things. Like, there might be less intricacy in the riffs because they were written in response to my voice.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.blabbermouth.net/news/all-that-remains-announces-madness-u-s-tour/|title=ALL THAT REMAINS Announces 'Madness' U.S. Tour|work=blabbermouth.net|date=March 14, 2017|accessdate=January 18, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Musical style==\nLabonte added that the majority of the new songs features \"significant programming and electronic sounds. And that's something we wanted to have flowing through the entire record. So you're gonna hear that kind of influence on most of the tracks.\" <ref name=\"blabbermouth.net\">{{cite web|url=http://www.blabbermouth.net/news/all-that-remains-singer-responds-to-sellout-accusations-says-there-is-plenty-of-heavy-material-on-upcoming-album/|title=ALL THAT REMAINS Singer Responds To 'Sellout' Accusations, Says There Is Plenty Of Heavy Material On Upcoming Album|work=blabbermouth.net|date=February 22, 2017|accessdate=January 18, 2018}}</ref>\n\nPhil also stated: \"On this record, there's five songs on the record that are exactly what you would expect from ''All That Remains''. There's some songs where we kind of were, like, 'All right, let's push this and maybe change what we can do, or what ''All That Remains'' is allowed to do.' But it ain't like we're not heavy anymore. And if you're just, like, 'Oh, they're not heavy anymore,' then you're just not listening.\"<ref name=\"blabbermouth.net\"/>\n\n==Reception==\nThe album received mixed reviews. Aaron J. Marko of ''[[Exclaim!]]'' described the album as mediocre, generic and archaic.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://exclaim.ca/music/article/all_that_remains-madness|title=All That Remains Madness|website=exclaim.ca|accessdate=January 18, 2018}}</ref> Christopher Di Carlo of Overdrive magazine,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://overdrive-mag.com/2017/05/30/album-review-all-that-remains-madness/|title=Album Review: All That Remains \u2013 Madness \u2013 Overdrive Music Magazine|work=Overdrive|date=May 30, 2017|accessdate=January 18, 2018}}</ref> on the other hand, described the album as beautiful yet heavy.\n\n==Track listing==\nAll lyrics written by Phil Labonte; all music composed by All That Remains.\n\n{{Track listing\n|title1 = Safe House\n|length1 = 3:37\n|title2 = Madness\n|length2 = 3:24\n|title3 = Nothing I Can Do\n|length3 = 3:41\n|title4 = If I'm Honest\n|length4 = 4:25\n|title5 = Halo\n|length5 = 4:03\n|title6 = Louder\n|length6 = 3:11\n|title7 = Rivercity\n|length7 = 5:33\n|title8 = Open Grave\n|length8 = 3:42\n|title9 = Far from Home\n|length9 = 4:05\n|title10 = Trust and Believe\n|length10 = 3:14\n|title11 = Back to You\n|length11 = 3:25\n|title12 = Never Sorry\n|length12 = 3:37\n|title13 = [[The Thunder Rolls#All That Remains cover version|The Thunder Rolls]]\n|note13 = [[Garth Brooks]] cover\n|length13 = 4:22\n|total_length = 50:17\n}}\n\n==Personnel==\n===All That Remains===\n* [[Philip Labonte]] \u2013 [[Lead vocalist|lead vocals]], art direction, cover design\n* Oli Herbert \u2013 [[lead guitar]]\n* Mike Martin \u2013 [[rhythm guitar]]\n* Aaron Patrick \u2013 [[bass guitar]], backing vocals\n* [[Jason Costa]] \u2013 [[Drum kit|drums]]\n\n===Additional musicians===\n*Mark Sereikas - additional guitar on \"Thunder Rolls\"\n*Benny Goodman - piano/keyboards and additional engineering/production on Thunder Rolls at Speak EZ Studios, Randolph, MA\n*Cory Paza - bass and additional engineering/production on Thunder rolls at Speak EZ Studios, Randolph, MA\n\n====Freedom Chorus====\n*[[Diamante (musician)|Diamante]] (also does additional vocals on \"Thunder Rolls\")\n*Meron Ryan\n*Sidnie Tipton\n*Lenny Skolnik\n*Seann Bowe\n\n===Production===\n* [[Howard Benson]] \u2013 production, mixing\n* Mike Plotnikoff \u2013 co-production, engineering\n* Hatsukazu \"Hatch\" Inagaki \u2013 engineering\n* Shaun Ezrol and Carl Stoodt \u2013 assistant engineering\n* [[Bob Ludwig]] \u2013 mastering \n* Lenny Skolnik, Seann Bowe, Howard Benson \u2013 keyboards and programming\n* Marc VanGool \u2013 guitar tech\n* Jon Nicholson at Drum Fetish \u2013 drum tech\n* Joe Rickard \u2013 pre-production, drum programming\n* Igor Khoroshev \u2013 string arrangement on \"Back to You\"\n* Paul DeCarli \u2013 digital editing\n* Nick Haussling \u2013 A&R\n* Tom Gnolfo \u2013 A&R administration\n* Diamante Azzura \u2013 backing vocals\n* [[The White Noise|Josh Strock]] \u2013 composition<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.allmusic.com/artist/josh-strock-mn0003478209|title=Josh Strock \u2013 Credits \u2013 AllMusic|website=AllMusic|accessdate=January 18, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Charts==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Chart (2017)\n! scope=\"col\"| Peak<br /> position\n|-\n{{album chart|BillboardCanada|77|artist=All That Remains|rowheader=true|accessdate=May 9, 2017}}\n|-\n{{album chart|Billboard200|50|artist=All That Remains|rowheader=true|accessdate=May 9, 2017}}\n|-\n{{album chart|BillboardRock|9|artist=All That Remains|rowheader=true|accessdate=May 9, 2017}}\n|-\n{{album chart|BillboardHardRock|1|artist=All That Remains|rowheader=true|accessdate=May 20, 2017}}\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n{{All That Remains}}\n\n[[Category:2017 albums]]\n[[Category:All That Remains (band) albums]]\n[[Category:Razor & Tie albums]]\n[[Category:Albums produced by Howard Benson]]\n", "name_user": "191.125.163.122", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Madness_(All_That_Remains_album)"}
{"title_page": "Victim of the New Disease", "text_new": "{{Infobox album\n| name       = Victim of the New Disease\n| type       = Studio\n| artist     = [[All That Remains (band)|All That Remains]]\n| cover      = ATRVictimoftheNewDisease.jpg\n| alt        =\n| released   = November 9, 2018\n| recorded   = 2018\n| studio     =\n| genre      = [[Melodic metalcore]]\n| length     = 39:02\n| label      = {{hlist|[[Razor & Tie]]}}\n| producer   = Daniel Laskiewicz<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.instagram.com/p/Bn6U58dg5MV/?taken-by=philthatremains|title=Photo|website=www.instagram.com}}</ref>\n| prev_title = [[Madness (All That Remains album)|Madness]]\n| prev_year  = 2017\n| next_title =\n| next_year  =\n| misc       = {{Singles\n | name        = Victim of the New Disease\n | type        = Studio\n | single1     = Fuck Love\n | single1date = September 17, 2018\n | single2     = Everything's Wrong\n | single2date = October 12, 2018\n | single3     = Wasteland\n | single3date = October 12, 2018\n | single4     = Just Tell Me Something\n | single4date = September 12, 2019\n}}\n}}\n\n'''''Victim of the New Disease''''' is the ninth studio album by American heavy metal band, [[All That Remains (band)|All That Remains]]. It was released on November 9, 2018<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.blabbermouth.net/news/all-that-remains-victim-of-the-new-disease-release-date-track-listing-revealed/|title=ALL THAT REMAINS: 'Victim Of The New Disease' Release Date, Track Listing Revealed|date=28 September 2018|publisher=}}</ref> on [[Razor & Tie]] Records. It is the final album to feature founding guitarist Oli Herbert, who died on October 17, 2018, less than a month prior to the album's release.<ref>{{cite web |title=LL THAT REMAINS Guitarist OLI HERBERT Dies |url=http://www.blabbermouth.net/news/all-that-remains-guitarist-oli-herbert-dies/ |website=[[Blabbermouth.net]] |accessdate=2018-10-17}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Bienstock |first1=Richard |title=All That Remains Guitarist Oli Herbert Has Died |url=https://www.guitarworld.com/news/all-that-remains-guitarist-oli-herbert-has-died |website=[[Guitar World]] |accessdate=2018-10-17}}</ref> The album marks a return to the band's heavier [[metalcore]] roots. ''Victim of the New Disease'' sold over 5,300 copies in the United States in its first week of release to land at position No. 154 on Billboard 200 chart.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.metalinsider.net/columns/metal-by-numbers/metal-by-numbers-11-21-holy-holiday-hell|title=Metal By Numbers 11/21: Holy holiday hell|date=November 21, 2018|publisher=}}</ref> \n\n==Background==\nThe first single from the album was \"Fuck Love.\" It was first posted to lead singer Phil Labonte's Instagram page as a cryptographic binary code leading to an unlisted YouTube video.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.instagram.com/p/BnzSGUOnhkH|title=Photo|website=www.instagram.com}}</ref> The album was produced by Daniel Laskiewicz, formerly of the bands The Acacia Strain and Legend.\n\n==Reception==\n{{Album ratings\n| rev1      = ''[[Exclaim!]]''\n| rev1Score = {{Rating|9|10}}<ref>{{cite web|url=http://exclaim.ca/music/article/all_that_remains-victim_of_the_new_disease|title=All That Remains: Victim of the New Disease review|work=[[Exclaim!]]|first=Max|last=Morin|accessdate=November 10, 2018}}</ref>\n| rev2      = Heavy Magazine''\n| rev2Score = {{rating|4|5}}<ref>{{cite web|url=https://heavymag.com.au/remains-victim-new-disease/|title=All That Remains 'Victim of the New Disease'|work=Heavy Magazine|first=Mick|last=Brichall|accessdate=November 10, 2018}}</ref>\n| rev3      = Metal Injection\n| rev3score = {{rating|9|10}}<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.metalinjection.net/reviews/all-that-remains-victim-of-the-new-disease|title=Album Review: ALL THAT REMAINS Victim of the New Disease|work=Metal Injection|first = Amber | last= Stevens|accessdate=November 12, 2018}}</ref>\n}}\n\n''Victim of the New Disease'' has received critical acclaim from music critics, with praise being directed at a perceived return to creative and musical form as well as the return to All That Remains' heavier sound, which had largely been absent in recent material from the band in favor of a more melodic rock sound.{{citation needed|date=November 2018}}\n\nIn a positive review for ''[[Exclaim!]]'' magazine, author Max Morin wrote \"To say All That Remains are returning to their roots would oversimplify things. They have returned, but much smarter and more experienced \u2014 it's given their old formula new life. ''Victim of the New Disease'' has jerked All That Remains out of a decade long lull\" and gave the album nine out of ten stars.<ref>https://exclaim.ca/music/article/all_that_remains-victim_of_the_new_disease</ref>\n\n==Track listing==\n{{Track listing\n|all_lyrics = Phil Labonte\n|all_music = All That Remains\n|title1 = Fuck Love\n|length1 = 2:58\n|title2 = Everything's Wrong\n|length2 = 4:10\n|title3 = Blood I Spill\n|length3 = 3:39\n|title4 = Wasteland\n|length4 = 4:50\n|title5 = Alone in the Darkness\n|length5 = 3:29\n|title6 = Misery in Me\n|length6 = 4:10\n|title7 = Broken\n|length7 = 3:22\n|title8 = Just Tell Me Something\n|note8 = featuring [[Danny Worsnop]]\n|length8 = 4:55\n|title9 = I Meant What I Said\n|length9 = 4:31\n|title10 = Victim of the New Disease\n|length10 = 2:58\n|total_length = 39:02\n}}\n\n==Personnel==\n'''All That Remains'''\n* [[Philip Labonte]] \u2013 lead vocals\n* Oli Herbert \u2013 lead guitar\n* Mike Martin \u2013 rhythm guitar\n* Aaron Patrick \u2013 bass guitar, backing vocals\n* [[Jason Costa]] \u2013 drums\n\n'''Additional personnel'''\n* [[Danny Worsnop]] - guest vocals on \"Just Tell Me Something\"\n* Daniel Laskiewicz and Jim Fogarty - additional instrumentation\n\n'''Production'''\n* Daniel Laskiewicz \u2013 Producer\n* Jim Fogarty - engineering\n* Josh Wilbur - Mixing, mastering\n\n==Charts==\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Chart (2018)\n! scope=\"col\"| Peak<br /> position\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Australian Digital Albums ([[ARIA Charts|ARIA]])<ref>{{cite web|url=http://cdn.aria.com.au/pdfs/5CD8E6E8A53F8AA937206EF3328C802F0D4E512E3A5C7B2F8B0AD84A49DDBC58/ARIA%20Digital%20Albums%20Chart.pdf?seq=14|title=ARIA Australian Top 50 Digital Albums|publisher=[[Australian Recording Industry Association]]|date=November 19, 2018|accessdate=November 17, 2018}}</ref>\n| 47\n|-\n{{album chart|Billboard200|154|artist=All That Remains|rowheader=true|accessdate=November 20, 2018}}\n|-\n{{album chart|BillboardRock|28|artist=All That Remains|rowheader=true|accessdate=November 20, 2018}}\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{All That Remains}}\n\n[[Category:2018 albums]]\n[[Category:All That Remains (band) albums]]\n[[Category:Razor & Tie albums]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox album\n| name       = Victim of the New Disease\n| type       = Studio\n| artist     = [[All That Remains (band)|All That Remains]]\n| cover      = ATRVictimoftheNewDisease.jpg\n| alt        =\n| released   = November 9, 2018\n| recorded   = 2018\n| studio     =\n| genre      = [[Metalcore]]\n| length     = 39:02\n| label      = {{hlist|[[Razor & Tie]]}}\n| producer   = Daniel Laskiewicz<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.instagram.com/p/Bn6U58dg5MV/?taken-by=philthatremains|title=Photo|website=www.instagram.com}}</ref>\n| prev_title = [[Madness (All That Remains album)|Madness]]\n| prev_year  = 2017\n| next_title =\n| next_year  =\n| misc       = {{Singles\n | name        = Victim of the New Disease\n | type        = Studio\n | single1     = Fuck Love\n | single1date = September 17, 2018\n | single2     = Everything's Wrong\n | single2date = October 12, 2018\n | single3     = Wasteland\n | single3date = October 12, 2018\n | single4     = Just Tell Me Something\n | single4date = September 12, 2019\n}}\n}}\n\n'''''Victim of the New Disease''''' is the ninth studio album by American heavy metal band, [[All That Remains (band)|All That Remains]]. It was released on November 9, 2018<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.blabbermouth.net/news/all-that-remains-victim-of-the-new-disease-release-date-track-listing-revealed/|title=ALL THAT REMAINS: 'Victim Of The New Disease' Release Date, Track Listing Revealed|date=28 September 2018|publisher=}}</ref> on [[Razor & Tie]] Records. It is the final album to feature founding guitarist Oli Herbert, who died on October 17, 2018, less than a month prior to the album's release.<ref>{{cite web |title=LL THAT REMAINS Guitarist OLI HERBERT Dies |url=http://www.blabbermouth.net/news/all-that-remains-guitarist-oli-herbert-dies/ |website=[[Blabbermouth.net]] |accessdate=2018-10-17}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Bienstock |first1=Richard |title=All That Remains Guitarist Oli Herbert Has Died |url=https://www.guitarworld.com/news/all-that-remains-guitarist-oli-herbert-has-died |website=[[Guitar World]] |accessdate=2018-10-17}}</ref> The album marks a return to the band's heavier [[metalcore]] roots. ''Victim of the New Disease'' sold over 5,300 copies in the United States in its first week of release to land at position No. 154 on Billboard 200 chart.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.metalinsider.net/columns/metal-by-numbers/metal-by-numbers-11-21-holy-holiday-hell|title=Metal By Numbers 11/21: Holy holiday hell|date=November 21, 2018|publisher=}}</ref> \n\n==Background==\nThe first single from the album was \"Fuck Love.\" It was first posted to lead singer Phil Labonte's Instagram page as a cryptographic binary code leading to an unlisted YouTube video.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.instagram.com/p/BnzSGUOnhkH|title=Photo|website=www.instagram.com}}</ref> The album was produced by Daniel Laskiewicz, formerly of the bands The Acacia Strain and Legend.\n\n==Reception==\n{{Album ratings\n| rev1      = ''[[Exclaim!]]''\n| rev1Score = {{Rating|9|10}}<ref>{{cite web|url=http://exclaim.ca/music/article/all_that_remains-victim_of_the_new_disease|title=All That Remains: Victim of the New Disease review|work=[[Exclaim!]]|first=Max|last=Morin|accessdate=November 10, 2018}}</ref>\n| rev2      = Heavy Magazine''\n| rev2Score = {{rating|4|5}}<ref>{{cite web|url=https://heavymag.com.au/remains-victim-new-disease/|title=All That Remains 'Victim of the New Disease'|work=Heavy Magazine|first=Mick|last=Brichall|accessdate=November 10, 2018}}</ref>\n| rev3      = Metal Injection\n| rev3score = {{rating|9|10}}<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.metalinjection.net/reviews/all-that-remains-victim-of-the-new-disease|title=Album Review: ALL THAT REMAINS Victim of the New Disease|work=Metal Injection|first = Amber | last= Stevens|accessdate=November 12, 2018}}</ref>\n}}\n\n''Victim of the New Disease'' has received critical acclaim from music critics, with praise being directed at a perceived return to creative and musical form as well as the return to All That Remains' heavier [[metalcore]] sound, which had largely been absent in recent material from the band in favor of a more traditional [[heavy metal music|heavy metal]] and [[hard rock]] sound.{{citation needed|date=November 2018}}\n\nIn a positive review for ''[[Exclaim!]]'' magazine, author Max Morin wrote \"To say All That Remains are returning to their roots would oversimplify things. They have returned, but much smarter and more experienced \u2014 it's given their old formula new life. ''Victim of the New Disease'' has jerked All That Remains out of a decade long lull\" and gave the album nine out of ten stars.<ref>https://exclaim.ca/music/article/all_that_remains-victim_of_the_new_disease</ref>\n\n==Track listing==\n{{Track listing\n|all_lyrics = Phil Labonte\n|all_music = All That Remains\n|title1 = Fuck Love\n|length1 = 2:58\n|title2 = Everything's Wrong\n|length2 = 4:10\n|title3 = Blood I Spill\n|length3 = 3:39\n|title4 = Wasteland\n|length4 = 4:50\n|title5 = Alone in the Darkness\n|length5 = 3:29\n|title6 = Misery in Me\n|length6 = 4:10\n|title7 = Broken\n|length7 = 3:22\n|title8 = Just Tell Me Something\n|note8 = featuring [[Danny Worsnop]]\n|length8 = 4:55\n|title9 = I Meant What I Said\n|length9 = 4:31\n|title10 = Victim of the New Disease\n|length10 = 2:58\n|total_length = 39:02\n}}\n\n==Personnel==\n'''All That Remains'''\n* [[Philip Labonte]] \u2013 lead vocals\n* Oli Herbert \u2013 lead guitar\n* Mike Martin \u2013 rhythm guitar\n* Aaron Patrick \u2013 bass guitar, backing vocals\n* [[Jason Costa]] \u2013 drums\n\n'''Additional personnel'''\n* [[Danny Worsnop]] - guest vocals on \"Just Tell Me Something\"\n* Daniel Laskiewicz and Jim Fogarty - additional instrumentation\n\n'''Production'''\n* Daniel Laskiewicz \u2013 Producer\n* Jim Fogarty - engineering\n* Josh Wilbur - Mixing, mastering\n\n==Charts==\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Chart (2018)\n! scope=\"col\"| Peak<br /> position\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Australian Digital Albums ([[ARIA Charts|ARIA]])<ref>{{cite web|url=http://cdn.aria.com.au/pdfs/5CD8E6E8A53F8AA937206EF3328C802F0D4E512E3A5C7B2F8B0AD84A49DDBC58/ARIA%20Digital%20Albums%20Chart.pdf?seq=14|title=ARIA Australian Top 50 Digital Albums|publisher=[[Australian Recording Industry Association]]|date=November 19, 2018|accessdate=November 17, 2018}}</ref>\n| 47\n|-\n{{album chart|Billboard200|154|artist=All That Remains|rowheader=true|accessdate=November 20, 2018}}\n|-\n{{album chart|BillboardRock|28|artist=All That Remains|rowheader=true|accessdate=November 20, 2018}}\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{All That Remains}}\n\n[[Category:2018 albums]]\n[[Category:All That Remains (band) albums]]\n[[Category:Razor & Tie albums]]\n", "name_user": "191.125.163.122", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Victim_of_the_New_Disease"}
