{"title_page": "Color Esperanza", "text_new": "{{Infobox song\n| name       = Color Esperanza\n| cover      = Color Esperanza single cover.jpg\n| alt        =\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[Diego Torres (singer)|Diego Torres]]\n| album      = [[Un Mundo Diferente]]\n| released   = May 16, 2002 <small>(US)<ref name= ColiTun>[https://www.amazon.com/dp/B000093FGT \"Color Esperanza\" single by Diego Torres] [[Amazon.com]] Accessed May 27-2010</ref>\n| format     = [[CD single]], [[Music download|digital download]]\n| recorded   = 2001\n| studio     =\n| venue      =\n| genre      = [[Latin pop]], [[candombe]], [[World music|world]]\n| length     = 4:27\n| label      = [[Sony Records|Sony Latin]]\n| writer     = [[Cachorro L\u00f3pez]], [[Coti Sorokin]], [[Diego Torres (singer)|Diego Torres]]\n| producer   = Cachorro L\u00f3pez, Diego Torres <small>(co-producer)\n| chronology = [[Diego Torres (singer)|Diego Torres]]\n| prev_title = D\u00f3nde Van\n| prev_year  = 2000\n| next_title = Sue\u00f1os\n| next_year  = 2002\n}}\n\"'''Color Esperanza'''\" (approximately in English: ''The \"Hope\" Color'') is the [[lead single]] from [[Diego Torres (singer)|Diego Torres]]'s fifth [[studio album]] ''[[Un Mundo Diferente]]''.\n\n==Lyrical content and background==\nThe song's lyrics reflect on themes of hope and overcoming hard times in life and the song's uplifting beat reflects the lyrical themes. The song was written by Coti Sorokin along with Cachorro L\u00f3pez and Spanish journalist Paco Garc\u00eda Caridad. The song was performed on [[MTV Unplugged (Diego Torres album)|MTV Unplugged]] featuring group La Chilinguita.\n\n==Special performance for the Pope John Paul II==\nIn 2003, the song was performed specially by Torres for the [[Pope John Paul II]] in [[Cuatro Vientos Airport]] in [[Madrid, Spain]] by the festival of the Youth, in order to welcome the Pope.<ref>[http://www.mtvla.com/news/articles/1471704/20030505/story.jhtml Diego Torres le canta \"Color Esperanza\" al Papa] (in Spanish) [[MTV|MTVla.com]]</ref>\n\n==Music video==\n[[Image:Color Esperanza music video.JPG|thumb|left|160px|Diego in the music video.]]\nA [[music video]] for the song was directed by Nahuel Lerena and Eduardo Pinto with whom Torres has worked in previous videos.\n\nWith a simple plot, the video begins with Torres sleeping in a bed, where he later begins to dream and finds himself in a forest where the landscape is green with a beautiful lake where everything revolves around the song.\n\nThe music video was nominated for the video of the year on the [[MTV Video Music Awards Latinoam\u00e9rica 2002]].\n\n'''Cover versions'''\n*The song has been covered on several singing talent contests as are [[La Academia]], [[Objetivo Fama]], etc.\n*[[Daniela Romo]] covered the song for her 2008 album [[Sue\u00f1os de Cabaret]].\n{{clear}}\n*In 2013 several Spanish female singers covered the song for the project ''Por ellas'', an initiative against breast cancer. Their version of ''Color esperanza'' became a number one hit in Spain.\n\n==Charts==\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n!align=\"left\"|Chart (2002)\n!align=\"left\"|Peak<br />position\n|-\n|U.S. ''[[Billboard magazine|Billboard]]'' [[Hot Latin Tracks|Hot Latin Songs]]<ref name= DieBill>[{{Allmusic|class=artist|id=p206881/charts-awards/billboard-singles|pure_url=yes}} Diego Torres > Billboard Chart History] at [[Allmusic|Allmusic.com]]</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|48\n|-\n|U.S. ''[[Billboard magazine|Billboard]]'' [[Billboard charts|Latin Pop Songs]]<ref name= DieBill />\n|align=\"center\"|26\n|-\n|U.S. ''[[Billboard magazine|Billboard]]'' [[Latin Tropical Airplay|Tropical Songs]]<ref name= DieBill />\n|align=\"center\"|12\n|-\n!align=\"left\"|Chart (2008)\n!align=\"left\"|Peak<br />position\n|-\n|Spain ([[PROMUSICAE]])<ref name= DieSpa>[http://spanishcharts.com/showitem.asp?interpret=Diego+Torres&titel=Un+mundo+diferente&cat=a Diego Torres > Spanish Charts] Spanishcharts.com</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|11\n|-\n! align=\"left\"| Chart (2020)\n!align=\"left\"|Peak<br />position\n|-\n|Colombia Pop ([[Monitor Latino]])<ref>{{cite web|url=http://charts.monitorlatino.com/top20/Print/Colombia/pop/20200330|title=Monitor Latino 2020 \u2013 Colombia Pop|publisher=[[Monitor Latino]]}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|8\n|-\n|}\n\n==See also==\n*[[List of number-one singles of 2013 (Spain)]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{YouTube|2Hay0xlAEwI|\"Color Esperanza\" music video}}\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20110710124126/http://www.diegotorres.com/english/index.php Diego Torres's official website]\n* {{MetroLyrics song|diego-torres|color-esperanza}}<!-- Licensed lyrics provider -->\n\n{{Diego Torres}}\n\n[[Category:2001 songs]]\n[[Category:2002 singles]]\n[[Category:Diego Torres songs]]\n[[Category:Sony BMG singles]]\n[[Category:Number-one singles in Spain]]\n[[Category:Song recordings produced by Cachorro L\u00f3pez]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Diego Torres]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Coti]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Cachorro L\u00f3pez]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox song\n| name       = Color Esperanza\n| cover      = Color Esperanza single cover.jpg\n| alt        =\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[Diego Torres (singer)|Diego Torres]]\n| album      = [[Un Mundo Diferente]]\n| released   = May 16, 2002 <small>(US)<ref name= ColiTun>[https://www.amazon.com/dp/B000093FGT \"Color Esperanza\" single by Diego Torres] [[Amazon.com]] Accessed May 27-2010</ref>\n| format     = [[CD single]], [[Music download|digital download]]\n| recorded   = 2001\n| studio     =\n| venue      =\n| genre      = [[Latin pop]], [[candombe]], [[World music|world]]\n| length     = 4:27\n| label      = [[Sony Records|Sony Latin]]\n| writer     = [[Cachorro L\u00f3pez]], [[Coti Sorokin]], [[Diego Torres (singer)|Diego Torres]]\n| producer   = Cachorro L\u00f3pez, Diego Torres <small>(co-producer)\n| chronology = [[Diego Torres (singer)|Diego Torres]]\n| prev_title = D\u00f3nde Van\n| prev_year  = 2000\n| next_title = Sue\u00f1os\n| next_year  = 2002\n}}\n\"'''Color Esperanza'''\" (approximately in English: ''The \"Hope\" Color'') is the [[lead single]] from [[Diego Torres (singer)|Diego Torres]]'s fifth [[studio album]] ''[[Un Mundo Diferente]]''.\n\n==Lyrical content and background==\nThe songs lyrics reflect on themes of hope and overcoming hard times in life and the song's uplifting beat reflects the lyrical themes. The song was written by Coti Sorokin along with Cachorro L\u00f3pez and Spanish journalist Paco Garc\u00eda Caridad. The song was performed on [[MTV Unplugged (Diego Torres album)|MTV Unplugged]] featuring group La Chilinguita.\n\n==Special performance for the Pope John Paul II==\nIn 2003, the song was performed specially by Torres for the [[Pope John Paul II]] in [[Cuatro Vientos Airport]] in [[Madrid, Spain]] by the festival of the Youth, in order to welcome the Pope.<ref>[http://www.mtvla.com/news/articles/1471704/20030505/story.jhtml Diego Torres le canta \"Color Esperanza\" al Papa] (in Spanish) [[MTV|MTVla.com]]</ref>\n\n==Music video==\n[[Image:Color Esperanza music video.JPG|thumb|left|160px|Diego in the music video.]]\nA [[music video]] for the song was directed by Nahuel Lerena and Eduardo Pinto with whom Torres has worked in previous videos.\n\nWith a simple plot, the video begins with Torres sleeping in a bed, where he later begins to dream and finds himself in a forest where the landscape is green with a beautiful lake where everything revolves around the song.\n\nThe music video was nominated for the video of the year on the [[MTV Video Music Awards Latinoam\u00e9rica 2002]].\n\n'''Cover versions'''\n*The song has been covered on several singing talent contests as are [[La Academia]], [[Objetivo Fama]], etc.\n*[[Daniela Romo]] covered the song for her 2008 album [[Sue\u00f1os de Cabaret]].\n{{clear}}\n*In 2013 several Spanish female singers covered the song for the project ''Por ellas'', an initiative against breast cancer. Their version of ''Color esperanza'' became a number one hit in Spain.\n\n==Charts==\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n!align=\"left\"|Chart (2002)\n!align=\"left\"|Peak<br />position\n|-\n|U.S. ''[[Billboard magazine|Billboard]]'' [[Hot Latin Tracks|Hot Latin Songs]]<ref name= DieBill>[{{Allmusic|class=artist|id=p206881/charts-awards/billboard-singles|pure_url=yes}} Diego Torres > Billboard Chart History] at [[Allmusic|Allmusic.com]]</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|48\n|-\n|U.S. ''[[Billboard magazine|Billboard]]'' [[Billboard charts|Latin Pop Songs]]<ref name= DieBill />\n|align=\"center\"|26\n|-\n|U.S. ''[[Billboard magazine|Billboard]]'' [[Latin Tropical Airplay|Tropical Songs]]<ref name= DieBill />\n|align=\"center\"|12\n|-\n!align=\"left\"|Chart (2008)\n!align=\"left\"|Peak<br />position\n|-\n|Spain ([[PROMUSICAE]])<ref name= DieSpa>[http://spanishcharts.com/showitem.asp?interpret=Diego+Torres&titel=Un+mundo+diferente&cat=a Diego Torres > Spanish Charts] Spanishcharts.com</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|11\n|-\n! align=\"left\"| Chart (2020)\n!align=\"left\"|Peak<br />position\n|-\n|Colombia Pop ([[Monitor Latino]])<ref>{{cite web|url=http://charts.monitorlatino.com/top20/Print/Colombia/pop/20200330|title=Monitor Latino 2020 \u2013 Colombia Pop|publisher=[[Monitor Latino]]}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|8\n|-\n|}\n\n==See also==\n*[[List of number-one singles of 2013 (Spain)]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{YouTube|2Hay0xlAEwI|\"Color Esperanza\" music video}}\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20110710124126/http://www.diegotorres.com/english/index.php Diego Torres's official website]\n* {{MetroLyrics song|diego-torres|color-esperanza}}<!-- Licensed lyrics provider -->\n\n{{Diego Torres}}\n\n[[Category:2001 songs]]\n[[Category:2002 singles]]\n[[Category:Diego Torres songs]]\n[[Category:Sony BMG singles]]\n[[Category:Number-one singles in Spain]]\n[[Category:Song recordings produced by Cachorro L\u00f3pez]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Diego Torres]]\